text.section:
Except as otherwise provided in the time-share instrument, the managing entity has the power to:
Institute, defend, or intervene in litigation or other legal proceedings in its own name on behalf of itself or 2 or more time-share owners on matters affecting time-shares, time-share units, or the time-share project;
Adopt and amend reasonable rules and regulations;
Indemnify its directors and officers and maintain directors' and officers' liability insurance with respect to the time-share project;
Impose charges for late payments of assessments and, after notice and an opportunity to be heard, levy reasonable fines for violation of the time-share instrument, bylaws, and rules and regulations of the time-share project; and
Exercise any other powers necessary and proper for the governance and operation of the time-share project.
